---
import DetailPage from "../../layouts/DetailPage.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Section.astro";
import KeyPoints from "../../components/KeyPoints.astro";
---

<DetailPage
  title="PyCxsim"
  meta="Open source · April 2023 – ongoing"
  backHref="/projects"
  backLabel="Projects"
  externalHref="https://github.com/Aatamte/PyCxsim"
  externalLabel="GitHub · pip install pycxsim"
>
  <p>An open-source Python framework for simulating autonomous agents in configurable environments. Inspired by complex adaptive systems research, Generative Agents (Park et al. 2023), and LLMs as Economic Agents (Horton 2023).</p>

  <Section title="What It Does">
    <KeyPoints points={[
      "Configurable environments where agents interact according to defined rules",
      "Real-time graphical interface for monitoring and controlling agent behavior during simulation",
      "Modular architecture supporting various agent types and interaction protocols",
    ]} />
  </Section>

  <Section title="Motivation">
    <p>Exploring how agents behave in simulated economic and political environments — what happens when you give LLM-based agents resources, goals, and the ability to trade, negotiate, or compete.</p>
  </Section>
</DetailPage>
